import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['pressure'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['pressure'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['pressure'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Median')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of pressure in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['date', 'temperature'])
    data = data.sort_values(by=['date'])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['temperature'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Temperature')
    ax.axhline(y=data['temperature'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Average Temperature: {data['temperature'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average temperature in Seattle?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['hour'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date']).dt.hour
    data['time_of_day'] = ['day' if (hour >= 6 and hour < 18) else 'night' for hour in data['hour']]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.boxplot([data[data['time_of_day'] == 'day']['temperature'], data[data['time_of_day'] == 'night']['temperature']])
    ax.set_xticklabels(['Day', 'Night'])
    ax.set_ylabel('Temperature')
    ax.axhline(data['temperature'].mean(), color='r', label=f'Mean: {data["temperature"].mean():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average temperature during the day and night?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
